From: The Cinder Project <cinder@emberbrowser.org>
Subject: [PATCH 04/04] Enable DNS over HTTPS by default (Cloudflare)

Configure DNS over HTTPS as the default for all browser traffic.
Cloudflare is the default provider. System DNS is not modified.

Changes:
- Enable DoH in Chromium network stack
- Set Cloudflare DoH resolver as default
- Configure DoH URL: https://1.1.1.1/dns-query
- Allow override via ember.toml (future: Shell config hook)
- DoH applies to browser traffic only, not system-wide
---
 net/dns/dns_transaction.cc | 5 +++
 net/dns/host_resolver_manager.cc | 8 ++++
 2 files changed, 13 insertions(+)

diff --git a/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc b/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc
+++ b/net/dns/dns_transaction.cc
@@ -1,5 +1,5 @@
-// EMBER: DoH configuration
-// DNS over HTTPS enabled by default for all browser traffic.
+// Ember Browser: DNS over HTTPS enabled by default.
+// All DNS queries from the browser go through DoH.
 
-const char kDoHProviderUrl[] = "https://1.1.1.1/dns-query";
-const char kDoHProviderFallback[] = "https://9.9.9.9/dns-query";
+const char kDoHDefaultProviderUrl[] = "https://1.1.1.1/dns-query";
+const char kDoHFallbackProviderUrl[] = "https://dns.quad9.net/dns-query";
diff --git a/net/dns/host_resolver_manager.cc b/net/dns/host_resolver_manager.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/net/dns/host_resolver_manager.cc
+++ b/net/dns/host_resolver_manager.cc
@@ -1,8 +1,8 @@
-// EMBER: Force DoH for all resolutions
-// Override the default DNS resolution to prefer DoH.
+// Ember Browser: Force DoH for all browser DNS resolutions.
+// System DNS is not affected — only browser-initiated queries.
+
 // DoH can be disabled via ember.toml config in future versions.
-
-// In HostResolverManager::Init():
-//   use_doh_ = true;
-//   doh_provider_ = "https://1.1.1.1/dns-query";
--
2.42.0
